\chapter{1947 Bell Centenary}

\begin{marginfigure}
\includegraphics[width=1.0\textwidth]{../canada/1947-Bell-Centenary.jpg}
\caption{Bell Centenary Stamp.}
\end{marginfigure}

Issued to commemorate the centenary of Alexander Graham Bell, the inventor of the telephone. 

\section{Design}

Shows Bell's portrait with the symbolic figure of "Fame" standing on the globe with a telegraph pole and wires in the upper left.

\section{Imprint}

In teh four corners of the sheet.

\section{Varieties}


A deep blue shade is unusual.

Prior to 1947 the Canadian Post office re-organized their internal arrangements and no further supplies of illegitimate imperforates came on the market. Also the leakage of die proofs ceased and we are only able to chronicle what is known to us to exist.
